name: Calamity Infernum +Apachii Classes + Remnants Map
description:
Tired of having to create structures with grandeur design that takes forever to build? Just want to hop in action and slay eldritch horrors beyond mortal comprehension? Look no further!

This map was made with Calamity Infernum, Remnants and Apachii's Classes Mod and it's purely untouched. You can choose not to install Apachii's Classes mod, but there may be some unloaded pink tiles here and there caused by the Lost Rune Fragment tile. Forgot to turn it off while making this world, sorry about that: As for the teleportation hub in the treehouse section, I only added a sky arena. Feel free to make your own arena.
Regardless, most of the buildings are from other map mods here in Curse Forge such as Ultirarria and Christmas Village (credits to both v0id585 and BlueJay_T_Gaming for the wonderful structures). Suffice to say, this world has every Calamity essentials generated (Sunken sea, Hallowed Garden, Planetoids, and even Vernal Soil biome added by yours truly). Have fun!

OPTIONAL: 
Also, Magic Storage is included, located beneath the church. I also made an alternate map that doesn't have any Magic Storage in case that you don't have it installed. You can choose not to use the Magic Storage mod, but I highly recommend it given how many items Calamity has, or Stars Above, if that's up to your speed.

name: The Torched Alchemy
description:
There is tiny item-transmuting map!
Use setup of two campfires to transmute torches, lighting right campfire first, then lighting left campfire stub, placing torches under right campfire, then clicking on blinking part of right campfire!
The leftmost block of three blocks between campfire will determine the direction of the CGO! To update it, update block above lihzahrd brick down in middle of 2 campfires, by placing torch, or toggling gemspark block, or toggling active/actuated block, or toggling conveyor belt. To get more torches, copy the crystal in the gap by that lihzahrd brick and hammered platform, then exchange it to torches by the merchant included!

name: Shimmering Skyblock
description:
This is a Skyblock survival map with added Shimmer. You only start with a chest with one Jungle seed and that's it! It is highly recommended to play as a Mediumcore player in order to progress unless playing in Journey mode. It is possible to progress as a Classic Character but it is extremally grindy at the start. There is a Demon Alter 377 blocks straight down. The "Dungeon" is 1,297 blocks to the east and the Lihzahrd Alter is 764 blocks west and 369 blocks down. Good luck!

Tips:
Simply throw your copper items into the shimmer and collect the copper ore and wood. Jump off and die to reset your tools and repeat. You can turn the ore and wood into stone and dirt as well
Making housing out of stone is faster than gathering wood
Once you have a house and 50 silver coins, you can buy anvils from the Merchant for iron equipment
Make an iron bucket and head down to the Underworld to gather lava from Lava Slimes and turn that into a bucket of water to unlock fishing as well as making a Jungle with those seeds
Once you defeat the Eye of Cthulhu you can buy Grass seeds and acorns from the Dryad
Turn potions into bottles and then into sand. You can make a Sandgun from turning mining potions into ingredients for Antlion Mandibles and getting topaz from Gem Bunnies or Squirrels
To get the Angler you will need at least 3 sandblocks in a 1x3 pattern and just a little bit of water for him to spawn

name: OneChunk
description:
OneChunk is a unique survival experience that confines your space to a single chunk of 128 blocks.
You find yourself on a solitary island, surrounded by infinite void.
Your task is to survive, utilizing the resources available within this one chunk.
Can you build a shelter, gather food, and survive using only what this small piece of the world offers?
This map is a real challenge for Terraria players who are looking for new and exciting ways to play.
Are you ready for the challenge? Remember, survival is just the beginning.
Your creativity and survival skills will be tested like never before. Good luck!

name: Terratale
description: Undertale is a game created by Toby Fox. This map is a recreation of his game and it's story as best as can be done. Terraria being a very different game from Undertale makes this map deviate in terms of gameplay. There are parkour challenges as oppose to standard puzzles like the ones seen in Undertale and the map has a metroidvania feel to it as well. This map is in the middle of development and content will keep being added even when the map is completed as a modded version and "Hard Mode" versions of the map must be added and zipped along with the original map.

name: Skyblock Islands
description:
This map is a simple skyblock that I created in my spare time, the map has 28 life crystals, enough for 2 or 3 people, but it is possible to get life crystals in the gold crates, all bosses are reachable, but how I made the map on mobile, it doesn't have a demonic altar (I was inspired by the skyblock Islands map to make the chest island)

List of islands:
(There are 3 types of islands: those in space, surface islands and underground islands)

Space:
Chest island (on top of the starting island): there is a chest with the starting items (such as: lava, honey water, etc.)
Fishing island: (to the left of the chest island): it is a fishing island with some bait
Dungeon island: (to the right of the chest island): it is the dungeon island

Ocean (also on the left)
Desert island (right)
Jungle Island (also on the right)

name: Coopventure 2
description:
Coopventure 2 is a two player cooperative puzzle map, which solely focuses on puzzles and platforming. It takes about 2-3 hours to complete.
Important: Most of the items and mechanics the map uses doesn't work properly on version 1.4, so you will have to use an earlier version.
Host a game, and set a password, so other random people can't accidentally join you. Invite your friend and wait for them to join, then you can start playing the map!
Some form of voice communication is highly recommended.

name: Micro World
description:
Remember back when Biah released Micro Terraria World, a map compressing the entire world into a small corner, having most every item obtainable from an older version of the game? Well, it's been a bunch of "final" updates since then, and Terraria has introduced a couple of new mini-biomes and structures, such as the underground desert, marble, granite, and shimmer.

Well this map has it all, folks! Spouting a little bit larger space, forcibly sized rather than built into a larger world of unbreakable bricks, every single natural chest item is included, along with a slew of crystal hearts, mana crystals, traps, floating islands, and a pre-built hallow biome so you don't have to worry about making your own once you hit hardmode!

name: Tree of Life
description:
This is "Tree of Life", a hand crafted giant living tree village in a large world infected by the crimson. The entire tree counts as valid housing, was designed to and can fit all of the NPC's, has a teleport system for easy travel, and large enough to be safe from blood moon spawns. The entrances are controlled by buttons only players can activate. Crimson should not be able to spread to it. Most of the game's crafting stations are present and most rooms feature their own furniture set - players can choose to remove if desired. It is insulated from meteors with cloud islands above (not pictured).
Very little other modification was done to this map except for some landscaping/coloring. The map has a pyramid, hidden sword shrine, and plenty of giant living trees/cloud islands. Check below the tree for a root that goes down to some mine cart tracks to get started underground.
Enjoy exploring!

description:
Subnautica is a survival game where the end goal is to escape the planet after being cured of the kharaa virus using the rocket(thats all the spoilers you get). This map aims to recreate Subnautica within the confines of 2D and with Terraria's limited colors and tiles to work with. Each biome in Terraria will translate to biomes from Subnautica, including the crash site and islands. I will be making new biomes based on the ones from Subnautica and eventually I will be implementing a whole "Arctic" biome as Subnautica is getting a DLC expansion with said biome.

name: SmallestBlock
description:
As you begin your journey, you'll find yourself on a minuscule island, isolated from the vast world. Your ingenuity and resourcefulness will be put to the test as you navigate the challenges that lie ahead. With only a handful of blocks and items at your disposal, you must carefully strategize your every move to thrive and complete the map.
One notable feature of this map is the introduction of a new liquid in Terraria version 1.4.4 called Shimmer. When you toss any item into the Shimmer, it undergoes a magical transformation. It can either be converted into a unique item or be deconstructed to yield essential resources that are vital for your progress. Utilize this mechanic wisely to maximize your chances of success.
Additionally, this map incorporates the "Get fixed boy" seed mechanic, a new addition to Terraria. By utilizing this seed, you can expect an increased level of difficulty, making your journey even more challenging. Prepare yourself for surprises as the drops from defeated enemies will continue to amaze and astound you.

name: Loot Only Challenge
description:
The goal is to beat the game with only items obtained from Monster drops! There are 24 Biome Islands and 10 Boss Arenas you can teleport to from a hub! The map comes with everything you will need to get started. The main housing area has the Guide, Arms Dealer, Goblin Tinkerer, Merchant and Nurse. There are 8 Locked Chests that contain Life Crystals and other accessories that aren‚Äôt necessary for completing but will help a lot. That‚Äôs about it!

Notes:
There are 6 Biome Chests that each have their respective Biome Chest Weapon and 2 accessories. There is a Golden Chest that contains 9 Life Crystals and some starter accessories but can only be opened after Skeletron is defeated.
There is a Locked Shadow Chest as well but it can only be reached once you have obtained a Rod of Discord, this chest has the remaining 6 life crystals in it

name: Simple Warehouse
description:
A simple warehouse that can be used for mass item storage.
Comes with the following:

name: Fish World Survival
description:
Welcome to Fish World Survival! The goal is to beat the game with items only obtained from Fishing and Angler Rewards. There are 16 Biome Islands, 10 boss arenas and a Shimmer Island you can teleport to from a hub. Each island is themed in their respective Biome. Map comes with all the items you will need to get started, also has Angler in the Ocean and Goblin Tinkerer in the Underground
Notes and Tips:
		There is a chest in the crafting room that has 10 life crystals to help speed up time, but they're locked behind a shadow chest!
		Collecting fallen stars while waiting for the next angler quest early is helpful, best place to get them is on the moon lord/mechanical boss arena
		Throwing unwanted potions into the Shimmer is useful for gathering ingredients for more useful potions
		Golden Keys are located in a chest in the dungeon, the Hellforge is in a locked chest in the crafting room
		Sometimes the Traveling Merchant will spawn on top of the biome islands or on a pillar platform and fall down to the underworld, he mostly spawns in with the Goblin Tinkerer though
		Set spawn point to the Ocean Biome bed to get to the Angler faster

name: Hazey Storage Center
description: This map was made using TEDIT, Storage Area with a couple statues, Surrounded by stone. This world is only for storage purposes, and has no other uses. Everything in the world was deleted and replaced with stone, and I added in my little custom storage center so you may use this world to organize some items and just have extra storage.

name: Brutal Skyblock
description:
What is a "skyblock" map?  It's a map where you start on an incredibly small "floating island" surrounded by void.  It may have a tree or water or lava on it, or it may literally just be dirt.  Often there are other small islands with different resources that you have to build to.  Why do people play skyblocks?  If you like a game, but are bored of it, a skyblock brings a fresh experience and new way to play.  It's also incredibly satisfying to start with nothing and build a whole world yourself, the way you want it to be.
So what makes Brutal Skyblock different and better than the other maps?
		It's harder.  You have to face real challenges even before you start fishing... unless you chose Baby Mode.
		It's easier too.  What?  The second island let's you select your skyblock difficulty: Baby, Veteran, or Brutal Legend.  It's 3 totally different maps in one!
		Completionism.  All bosses, events, NPC's, biomes, accessories, armor, traps, and 99% of weapons can be gotten in this map.
		Mobile compatible.  I use mobile map files.  When loaded on PC, the game just silently updates them.  No issues.
		Multiplayer friendly.  I give out just a little bit extra of certain non-renewable resources to make the map "comfortable" for about 4 players.
		Tiny! The world uses a crazy custom 2,000x800 block world size. About 1/2 the size of a small world.

name: SkyTerra
description:
Playing Skyblock, have you ever wondered about the possibilities of survival with a minimum of resources? Do you want to get a unique gaming experience in Terraria? This map is perfect for you!
You will appear on a small piece of land, in the middle of the void. Your task is to show your knowledge of Terraria and your resourcefulness to complete hidden in map tasks?
You can play SkyTerra with your friends. The files contains four versions of the map with different internal difficulty levels.

name: The Legend of Zelda
description:
Play as Link and fight your way through nine dungeons. Bring peace back to the land of Hyrule and save the princess Zelda!

12 Simple Rules - Create a new Journey Mode Character
1. Throw away your starting items, including Journey Mode wings and turn off Increased Placement Range.
2. You can only buy ammo, potions and throwable items like Shurikens from the vendors.
3. Player one should always grab the chest from the bottom center when four chests are in a triangle.
4. If there are two or more signs next to each other, always read left to right. Golden Tombstones should always be read.
5. Do not take the clothes off mannequins.
6. Weapons and potions dropped from enemies and bosses can be used except for Rope. Do not use Rope of any kind.
7. Crafting is allowed, like crafting Mana Crystals from Fallen Stars. Find workbenches, tinker's workshops, etc. in Mundus Village.
8. No placing blocks, except after defeating the Eye of Cthulhu where instructed to.
9. No breaking blocks, except in Ganondorf's Lair with the explosives given.
10. Read the signs carefully, as they point you in the proper direction and sometimes hint at secrets.
11. Research the Large Gems, as a safeguard, as they can be lost easily. Duplicate the Large Gems for their corresponding Gem Locks for upgrades and secrets! No other research/duplication should be done.
12. In Journey Mode, set the enemy difficulty to Classic or higher.
Multiplayer
Up to 4 players can coop through the adventure in Journey Mode!
The rules are the same as the single player rules.

name: Builder's Workshop
description:
Map Contents:
All placeable items currently in-game
All NPCs
At least four copies of most armor, tools, weapons, and accessories
A limited stock (mostly one stack each) of most crafting materials
Lots and lots of empty flat space.
The only thing on this world besides the buildings you spawn in is flat ground. It starts slightly above the underground and continues clear down into what would be hell. If you load this on a map viewer it is the most boring world in existence.
This does, however, make it a perfect place to design a dungeon, play with wiring systems and traps, or test different combinations of building materials to find a selection you like the look of.

name: COMPACT ALL ITEMS HUB
description:
Are you a Terraria Vet in the midst of a build and simply want the easiest and quickest access, directly to the block/s, item/s, or material/s your after?
Are you new to the game, and would like to start learning about, and building with all Terraria has to offer right from the get go?
Either way, your in the right place!
Allow me to introduce and welcome you to the "SUNV XTRA_ALL ITEMS-1.4+/2022! (PC & MOBILE!) WORLD!"
With this world in your Terraria world's list, you will have access to the easiest and quickest, most compact, 1.4+ ALL ITEM'S WORLD to date!...
(Granted you may need a day to familiarize yourself with the world, as you would any other!)
Once you have though, the Terraria universe is at your finger tips!
So, get your hands on the "SUNV XTRA_ALL ITEMS-1.4+/2022! (PC & MOBILE!)" world, and start your journey today!...

name: The Shimmer Lands
description:
The Shimmer Lands is a Custom ‚ÄòAll Items Map‚Äô & ‚ÄòAdventure Map‚Äô created to grant Terraria players across all platforms any Items they need as well as NPC‚Äôs, and beautiful housing to survive the night in, Having these things allows players to venture their own worlds, safely knowing enemy won‚Äôt stand a chance!
So loot up! Adventure up! Discover hidden secrets! Explore the Lands of Shimmery pools & crystal mountains, and take down End Game Bosses like a piece of cake.
This Map contains a Variety of Different features to explore and Discover. This is including:
-Every Item For Terraria 1.4.4 (onwards)
-Crystal Infested Mountains

This map is adventurous! There are many secret locations created for your personal entertainment and skills of survival!
Most importantly, this map was created with Love, Thoughts and creative ideas to produce an all items world With adventure.

name: Starter World
description:
World:
Medium
Corruption
All difficulties available
No bosses defeated and completely unexplored
The bases consist of:
1. A large farm
2. NPC housing
3. A crafting area
4. A storage area
5. A potion brewery  
6. A gel farm (other statues only drop items when hit by summon)
7. A centralized spawn area (initial spawn is the center of the base)
8. Dedicated fishing for almost every biome (Sky lake is right above arena)

10. An Etherian arena (Also works for invasions and blood moons, just stand on one side. Can also place Lihzahrd Altar underneath within the honey.)
11. 8 Pylons (Forest, Jungle, Ocean, Mushroom, Desert, Cavern, Hollow, and Snow). There is a hellevator in the Cavern base and the Desert pylon is near the Dungeon. Basic NPCs have been spawned to allow pylon usage with the exception of Hollow.

name: Khaiostomization
description:
This is a large vanilla world with crimson, where I built a detailed base, and customized dungeon. The base has a large crafting area (with early-game crafting stations readily available), large storage area, housing for all NPCs (as of version 1.3.5), fishing ponds for all angler quests, herb farm, glowing mushroom farm, and a hellevator with a miniature base at the bottom of it.
The dungeon has been completely customized from scratch. It has all of the loot you would expect to find within a dungeon, as well as an additional fishing pond, and safe area to set your spawn point. The entrance has been completely customized, but will still spawn the cultists in hardmode. The dungeon itself has unique challenges within it, as well as a half dozen secret areas. You can make it as easy or difficult as you'd like by mining and placing blocks, or trying the challenges without changing the dungeon. Explore, and have fun!

name: THE KINGDOM
description: It is a complete world with many farms, armory, library, space center and much much more.

name: All in One Map
description:
- Added an ocean cave.
- Made the sword shrine have a chest with both the sword and Terragrim.
- Added an extra chamber below the pyramid with the missing items from the chest.
- Added a graveyard, for Biome completeness and for hardcore characters.
- Added all Moss types. (NOTE Tedit did not handle Moss well, so I am not 100% sure this is working. I added all the moss types in a long line below the snow Biome If you wanted to know where to find them.)
- I added all Ore types both pre and post Hardmode. I did the pre-hardmode ores by mass replacing ore types in huge 200x200 lines spanning the whole map. Some are straight lines down, some are horizontal sections. The ores are pretty close to 50:50 each, but Copper and Tin are the closest, only a few 100 difference overall. Once in Hardmode, since the world counts as "Drunk" (NOTE The base seed is NOT a drunk seed. I changed to Drunk after initial world gen) as altars are broken you will get all 6 ore types.
- Added a few more Demon Altars to help get more ore types given you are getting 6 HM ore types vs 3.
- I added the removed Heart Shrine micro Biome in the Snow Biome, why? Because why not.
- Made one of the beehives larger than the rest.
- Speaking of Crimson, I added a Crimson chest with proper items into the Dungeon.
- Speaking of the Dungeon, made 3 colors preset in the world, replaced all items in each section with the proper brick,background, items, etc. I also added a bit of extra brick and background in some places, so if you want to build an arena in a certain color type, you should have plenty of space to do so.
- I added tons more temple traps, ~100 Spiky ball traps, ~25 Spear traps, ~10 flame traps.
- I made sure every chest item was spawned into the world at least once.
- I added every painting. (NOTE I am not 100% sure, Tedit updated mid way through my progress and it made placing sprites way harder, and I couldn't find paintings anymore. name: ShimmerBlock
description:
Can you progress from nothing but a small pool of Shimmer* all the way to defeating the Moon Lord?
Well, yes, as long as you're prepared to die... A lot.
As a twist on regular Skyblock maps, this one needs to be played on MediumCore, If you start on classic or hardcore, you'll quickly find there's almost nothing you can do to progress.

name: R'lyeh Nexus
description:
You are an inter-dimensional warrior tasked with a daunting quest: save the multiverse by destroying the Moon Lord in his home realm!  In order to confront him, you must first defeat his allies - each a lord of his own plane.  The order you confront them is up to you!
-1 to 3 players!
-Class specialization!
-Each boss has a reward item posted in the hub.  Devise your own strategies!
-Each stage has multiple hidden chests with extra loot!
-Hella bosses!
-Dramatically varied environments - every stage is its own dimension!
-Achievements! (E.G. beat bosses without using Healing Potions)
-Secret stuff!

name: Shimmering Skies
description:
SOFTLOCK PREVENTION
	-Keep a block/platform under the spawn point at all times to avoid falling death loops.
	-Don't spill the shimmer or lose the Lihzahrd Altar (obviously).
	-Don't break the Lihzahrd background wall. It can't be shimmered back into treacherous wall until Golem is dead.
	-Don't convert the ice all the way down to snow at the start, just because that's fewer blocks.
	-Don't kill the Skeletron Prime part of Mechdusa until you have killed the other parts at least once, or have plenty of spare mechanical skulls.

name: Red Hat Castle
description:
Red Hat Castle is a non-linear adventure map originally that's inspired by many influences from 80s, 90s and 2000s adventure titles, including Castlevania, Zelda, Metroid, and Dark Souls.  You explore a large castle and its surrounding zones on a quest to remove the king's curse.  There are 3 built-in difficulty settings, each with unique content and endings.  Just download the map, put it in your "worlds" folder and create a softcore character and you're ready to begin!
Features:
	Designed for 1 or 2 players!
	3 to 6-ish hours of gameplay per run
	Open-world, non-linear progression
	Unique and varied environments, some completely optional to visit
	Countless secrets off-the-beaten-path for observant and adventurous players

name: World Of Terra
description:
Experience Terraria in a brand new way with this exciting adventure that introduces a wide range of changes. This world has been transformed with the addition of several dungeons, golf courses, rest areas, stories, boss arenas, puzzles, and many other places and treasures to discover, all without altering the base game or its rules.
This map is perfect for starting a new game, whether you prefer to play alone or with a team. In short, the adventure awaits you!

Map Information:
Drunk mod
Available in classic, expert, master, and journey modes
No bosses have been defeated
Medium-sized world
No rules

name: All unobtainable items map
description:
What's a unobtainable item?
Unobtainable refers to fully functional (or partially functional) features which for some reason are unavailable during normal gameplay. They are only accessible through game modification software like inventory editors and tools like Terraria Tweaker, the latter which prevents automatic in-game removal of unobtainable items. Features may also be labeled as unobtainable due to being only partially obtainable
Unimplemented refers to features that are only partially present in the game files. Due to incomplete coding, being replaced by another feature (such as another item), or forced deletion, they cannot be accessed in-game, even with software like inventory editors. The only exception to this inaccessibility is the Boring Bow, which can be placed in the inventory.
Removed refers to features that have been completely removed from the game for various reasons, ranging from copyright liability to former-exclusivity. There is no longer any data related to them present in the game's files, and their Data IDs are typically replaced by something else.

name: Dark Souls Adventure Map: The Story of Red Cloud
description:
The Story of Red Cloud is a massive Dark Souls-inspired adventure built inside the world of Terraria using a custom map, mod and companion soundtrack.
Developed over 6 years, your 1-4 player journey will span 18 dungeons spread across an expansive, hand-crafted open world, offering a 20 to 30+ hr experience for a first playthrough.

TOP FEATURES
	*Companion Soundtrack with 59 songs! (Dark Souls, Elden Ring and Zelda fans will love it)
	*42 bosses (17 vanilla plus 25 mod bosses)
	*100+ new NPCS including 8 friendly NPCs
	*Over 800 new mod items, weapons, and armors, both original and remixed from two dozen of the best classic mods from the community
	*Dark Souls game mechanics, including bonfire save points and the dodge roll
	*The mod enforces old-school adventure map rules, so if you can do it, it's okay to do it!
	*800+ chests to loot, containing almost every item in base Terraria

description:

Rules of the game
	Don't break any blocks
	You and your friends must have the same type of equipment
	Some cards have a specific item that can be found in a glass chest. Everyone can use items from the chest, but only 1 item can be taken.
	Before starting a battle in the arenas, all players must have 400 HP and 200 mana.
	You cannot change accessories in the middle of the game (in the Arena)
	Some classes have style items and you must place them in style slots
	Do not interact with any NPC other than the nurse
	After using a class, you must put it in this class chest

name: Counter Strike
description:
Let's combine two popular games and have some Counter Strike-style fun with Terraria's game mechanics? The task of the map is simple, but not without peculiarities. The terrorists must get to the dungeon, kill the Skeletron and find the Mechanic in the Dungeon, buy wires and a wrench, and then try to connect a lever near the tower to explosives and, accordingly, blow up this tower.It's simple, right? The Counter-Terrarists have a simpler task, but no less important - while the Terrarists make their little journey for copper cable to hand it over to a collection point for non-ferrous metals by the wires to the Mechanic in Dungeon, the Counter-Terrarians must prepare to meet the ‚Äúguests‚Äù. How the preparations will take place - it all depends on your imagination and the time that you will have from the beginning of the game to the moment of meeting.

The card is designed for the number of players from two to eight people. Best of all, of course, eight, since there are 4 classes in the game and the most interesting game will turn out just with the full complement.

Player Classes:
	Demoman
	attack plane
	Sniper
	Heavy infantry
